observations.recommendation:
Municipal Treasurer prepares PCs for every class of PPE;

and the Municipal Accountant prepares PPELC, RPLC and CIPLC, and facilitates reconciliation with the balances in the books of accounts and PCs and RPCPPEs to be prepared by the MTO.

Inventory committee immediately conducts the physical inventory of all properties and submits the corresponding RPCPPE to the auditor as required under existing regulations.

We recommended and management agreed to direct:
1. The Municipal Treasurer to maintain and regularly update cashbooks and reconcile them with the Municipal Accountant’s subsidiary ledgers at least quarterly;
2. The Municipal Accountant to consistently prepare Bank Reconciliation Statements (BRS);
3. The Municipal Accountant to record all identified book reconciling items in the books; and
4. The Municipal Treasurer or Municipal Accountant to promptly correct any detected errors to ensure accurate financial records.
